properties.abstract: The Davos Valley Tour is particularly well suited for families and beginners. The uphill sections are all gentle and most of the tracks are easy to negotiate.
properties.description:
This pleasant tour is mainly on easily manageable tracks with only a few uphill sections in the surroundings of Davos. From the Sports Centre at Davos Platz we cross the valley road (Talstrasse) and cycle along the Mattastrasse towards the Jakobshorn valley station. There the cycle trail leads into a gentle uphill section across the Wildboden to the Sertig mill.

From the mill to Clavadel we cycle along another gentle uphill section. Through the Spinnelenwald forest, we cycle past the entire length of Davos to the lower Dischma valley. Via the Büelen a forest track takes us into the Flüela valley, where a fun single trail leads us back to Davos Dorf, where we pick up the cycle path back to Davos Platz and our starting point.
